    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-20T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="735"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d735">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1023</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-20T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.07 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10742. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 835. From <persName>Alfred G. Smith</persName> for <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName>. After discussing
                    with <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SRB1">Stevens</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> the
                    advisability of having a British expert assist me in Spanish negotiations I have
                    decided to accept such assistance on the understanding that you left in my hands
                    the decision on this point. At my request <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> has written a letter
                    to Foreign Office, of which the following is a paraphrase: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Regarding proposed negotiations by United States representatives for
                            tonnage agreement with Spain as contemplated by Spanish-American
                            agreement March 9 [<hi rend="italic">7</hi>], I confirm conversation
                            regarding participation of British Government in regard thereto. Mr.
                                <persName>Smith</persName>, representing War Trade Board and
                            Shipping Board, has special mission to assist United States Ambassador
                            in Madrid in conducting these negotiations. Mr.
                                <persName>Smith</persName> would be very pleased if His Majesty’s
                            Government should designate a shipping expert to assist him in
                            conducting these negotiations in Madrid and is also pleased to learn
                            that the British Commercial Attaché in Madrid will also be instructed to
                            assist him in these negotiations.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I am leaving for Paris to-morrow and expect to arrive in Madrid the early part of
                    next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
